ecent dream, Ash assembled the mighty Menage to help him explore Nagafen's Lair...the objective: to try and track down the source of his affliction.<br><br> The dungeon crawl was a success...with the guild's help, Ash managed to determine the source of his nightmares. An ancient fire spirit, channeled into the mortal world by Efreeti Lord Djarn, had latched on to his pyromaniac mind and was attempting to possess him...<br><br>  However, the success was double-edged. By bringing himself into close proximty with his tormentor, he had increased its hold over him. Only a self imposed exile to the frozen wastes of Velious could hold the demon at bay, the ice cooling the fires now raging in his subconscious.<br><br>  But Ash cant hide forever. The fire spirit has already grown strong enough to invade his dreams once more, even in the frozen fortress of Thurgadin. Only by eliminating the one who summoned the spirit into this world will he sever its hold over him...and be free.<br><br>  In short, the Efreeti Lord Must Die.<br><br>  Ash appeals to the Menage to help him slay Efreeti Lord Djarn. He must be present when the Efreet falls to rid himself of this curse. However, know this: should we fail, then Ash will not be able to resist the fire spirit a second time. It will complete its possession of him, and convert him into an agent of the Apocalypse.....He will be lost to you forever.<br><br><br>  ********************************<br>             Steel Menage Efreeti Raid<br>  ********************************<br><br>  Date: Tuesday 23rd October<br>  Time: 5pm Pacific, 7pm Central, 8pm Eastern, 1am GMT<br>  Meet: Lavastorm Mountains, Druid Ring<br>  Objectives: Fight way to Efreet Room.<br>                  Clear and hold Efreet Room till Efreet spawns.<br>                  Kill Efreet with Ash present<br><br>  Recommended level: Im guessing 40+, but Ill take all the<br>                              help i can get <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>  Notes: This is not a reservable mob, so its pot luck as to whether a group will be camping it or not. Apparently it needs a little teamwork to get to, and is fairly tough to crack, so we might be ok unless another guild is raiding it. Keep your fingers crossed. If its being camped when we turn up, Ill ask if we can have a stab at it within an hour or so...if not, then backup plan is to hit Kedge Keep again <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/umaglor01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>maglor01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(10/8/01 5:43:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fsteelmenagetheboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Efreeti Lord Must Die!!!</span><hr size=1> Tuesday 23 OCT dutifully marked on the calendar.  <br><br>I will be about 10 minutes or so late, though... the local constabulary takes exception to the kinds of speeds that would be required to get me there on time.<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>--Maglor<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ubuurn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Buurn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(10/9/01 12:15:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fsteelmenagetheboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScre